\id HEB - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project 
\h IPURU 
\toc1 Enno'sa' Kareta Ipuru Amʉ' Ena' 
\toc2 Ipuru 
\toc3 Ipuru 
\mt2 Enno'sa' Kareta 
\mt1 Ipuru Amʉ' 
\mt2 Ena' 
\imt1 Ekamanin 
\ip \bk Enno'sa' Kareta Ipuru Amʉ' Ena'\bk* e'menuka'pʉ tamu'kuru' tawon kon Kʉri'san amʉ' ena', tewa'nomanin kon epamʉ wenai Kʉri'san pe te'to' kon uya apurɨto' ɨnnonkapai te'san. Imenukanin uya to' pori'mapɨtʉ to' uya apurɨto' yau Sises Kʉrai esi i'nai rɨ Papa usenpoikasa' pe tukai' enpoika tʉuya winɨ kuru. Serɨ kupʉ tʉuya pɨ' osorʉwawon ton i'nairon ton pɨ' iyetʉ'kapɨtʉ: wapiya, Sises esi inkero' rɨ Papa Mumu pe, isenupasa' rʉ'pʉ i'nai rɨ main awɨrɨ e'nɨto' pɨ', Ikʉipʉnʉ pɨ' tekota'mato' tʉnmoronka'pʉ poro. Papa Mumu pe tesi ke, Sises esi eke pe pu'kena' amʉ' Penaro' Ekonekan nɨto' awon kon, inserʉ amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Mosi' rɨ entai. Itisakon pe, Papa uya Sises ekamasa' inkero' rɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe eke pe Penaro' Ekonekan nɨto' awon kon use'man nɨto' tʉrawasoma entai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itosorʉwano pe, Sises poro apurɨnin epika'tɨ makoi, enari'ke' pe te'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uma'tan nɨto' piyapai; Sises si use'man nɨto' epuru pe esii'ma uya si i'nai rɨ epika'tɨn nɨto' tʉrʉ, ento' ipɨ' pe iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ iku'to' pe inonkasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ o' ke use'man nɨto' Ipuru amʉ' ɨpʉremato' ekareei winɨ. 
\ip Ipan pe tʉnmenuka'pʉ ennin nan panama iya apurɨto' tʉuya'nokon yau to' uko'manto' pe miyarɨ iu'matʉ pʉ'kʉ pona, Sises pɨ' tenu kon tʉtʉse, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imoronkanin pe ɨ'rɨ rɨ ekota'man nɨto' esi a'tai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ yau tʉku'to' kon eporo tʉuya'nokon a'tai. Kareta uta'koro panaman nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ te'ku'ton pɨ' to' pana'tɨ pe. 
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin 
\io1 Ekamanin: Kʉrai iyenuka'sa' pe kuru rɨ Papa usenpoikato' iwinɨ (1:1-3) 
\io1 Eke pe Kʉrai e'to' inserʉ amʉ' entai (1:4—2:18) 
\io1 Eke pe Kʉrai e'to' Mosi' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isa'suwa entai (3:1—4:13) 
\io1 Eke pe Kʉrai e'to' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomato' iya yau (4:14—7:28) 
\io1 Eke pe Kʉrai e'to' emenna' tekonekasa' yau (8:1—9:22) 
\io1 Eke pe Kʉrai e'to' use'man nɨto' pe te'to' yau (9:23—10:39) 
\io1 Eke pe kuru apurɨto' esi (11:1—12:29) 
\io1 Papa pori'mato' (13:1-19) 
\io1 Uta'koron pe ɨpʉreman nɨto' (13:20-21) 
\io1 Iu'matʉ main (13:22-25) 
\c 1  
\s1 Imu Eke Inserʉ Amʉ' Entaino 
\p  
\v 1 Pena Papa uya utamokori kon amʉ' auro'kapɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ pu'kena' amʉ' poro tʉron nɨ a'tai'ne, tu'kan winɨ rɨ,  
\v 2 e'tane si serɨ ton iu'matʉ weyu ton a'tai'ne uyauro'kasa' iya 'nokon Tʉmu winɨ, tʉnanʉmʉ'pʉ tanporon nɨ anʉnnin pe iye'to' pe, iporo tanporon nɨ mɨ yawɨron kaa'pʉ iya na'ne'.  
\v 3 Imu esi te'wei'tɨsen Papa a'kwarii ke, mɨrɨpan esi kʉrɨ rɨ e'to' e' pe kuru rɨ, meruntɨ imaimu erupa' rɨ tanporon nɨ uko'mamʉ miyarɨ. Makoi ekorʉkato' tʉrʉ tʉpo, iyereuta'pʉ Eke emiyatʉ enwo'netʉ winɨ Epʉn po.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨpan si ena'pʉ eke pe inserʉ amʉ' entai, tese' tʉnanʉmʉ'pʉ esi eke pe to' ese' entai kasa. 
\p  
\v 5 Apʉne pʉra, nai kʉrɨ warai inserʉ pɨ' ken Papa, 
\q1 “Umu ɨmɨrɨ tikin nan kuru rɨ; serɨ pe ɨkʉipʉnʉ pe enasa',”\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Eren 2:7\f* 
\m tawon? Mɨrɨ pe pʉra kanan, 
\q1 “Ikʉipʉnʉ pe e'to' oton, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umu pe iye'to' oton,”\f + \fr 1:5 \ft 2 Sanwerʉ 7:14; 1 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 17:13\f* 
\m tawon?  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kanan, tɨmʉrewato' ennoko Papa uya a'tai non pona, 
\q1 “Tɨwɨ tanporo Papa inserʉʉi ton napurɨpɨtʉi,”\f + \fr 1:6 \ft Isu'taronomi 32:43 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 7 Inserʉ amʉ' pɨ' tʉusaurokʉ a'tai, 
\q1 “Uinserʉʉi ton kupʉ uya a'setun pe, 
\q2 upoitorʉ ton apo' e'werouwerouma pe,”\f + \fr 1:7 \ft Eren 104:4 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta iya.  
\v 8 E'tane si Imu pɨ', 
\q1 “Papa, ayapon e'to' oton inke rɨ, inke rɨ, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipokena' pe e'nɨto' itesa' pe ɨwesi yʉʉi pe. 
\q1  
\v 9 Ipoken e'nɨto' i'nʉnkasa' auya, ipoken pʉra e'nɨto' ewaruma'tɨsa' auya; 
\q2 mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Papa, itese' pɨ' ɨwe'to' uya ɨku'sa' ɨtonpa ton epoi, 
\q2 ɨmɨrɨ tʉkarapaimai' pori' pe ɨwesi ekamanin pe,”\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Eren 45:6-7\f* 
\m ta iya.  
\v 10 Tasa' iya rɨ marɨ, 
\q1 “Itepuru, iyepiya'tɨ yau non apon nonka'pʉ auya, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka' esi ɨyemiyatʉ ton tʉrawasooi rʉ'pʉ ton pe. 
\q1  
\v 11 Tʉuma'ta ton nɨ, ɨmɨrɨ moro rɨ; 
\q2 tanporo pon a'mota kasa ta'mota ton. 
\q1  
\v 12 Pon pʉro'pon e'mepɨtʉ kasa e'mepɨ'to' auya oton; 
\q2 pon usensima kasa isensimato' oton. 
\q1 E'tane ɨmɨrɨ moro mɨrɨ kasa rɨ, 
\q2 ɨukɨɨi'pamʉ pen nɨ,”\f + \fr 1:12 \ft Eren 102:25-27 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta iya.  
\v 13 Nai kʉrɨ warai inserʉ pɨ' ken, 
\q2 “Ereutakɨ, uyemiyatʉ enwo'netʉ winɨ 
\q1 ɨyeyaton non tʉrʉ uya pʉ'kʉ pona 
\q2 a'ta apon pe,”\f + \fr 1:13 \ft Eren 110:1\f* 
\m tawon Papa?  
\v 14 Inserʉ amʉ' pen pe' kamoro a'kwarʉ ton e'tʉrawasomai' enno'sa' kon kamo epika'tɨn nɨto' eponin nan apiyo' pe? 
\c 2  
\s1 Panaman Pana Tʉtʉse E'nɨto' Pe 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', etasa' rʉ'pʉ pɨ' upana kon tʉtʉse e'nɨpai'nokon, utano'man pe iyesi namai'.  
\v 2 Apʉne pʉra inserʉ amʉ' usauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ e'sa' pe iyesi yau iyawɨrɨ e'nɨto' kuru, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo mɨrɨ ton i'kwɨ'sa' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyawɨrɨ pʉra e'nɨsa' uya ipoken nɨ tʉkota'mato' eposa' yau,  
\v 3 nai kasa ekota'man nɨto' apai ainʉn nɨ eke rɨ epika'tɨn nɨto' anʉnsa' pʉra iye'tane? Serɨ epika'tɨn nɨto', wapiya kuru Itepuru nekama'pʉ rʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan akonomasa' etanin nʉ'san uya upana kon ya'.  
\v 4 Papa uya rɨ kanan ekamasa' mɨrɨ pona ento' ipɨkɨrɨ ke, enuminkanin ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ti'tui' pʉra eke tʉtʉrawasooi ton ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Wakʉ A'kwarʉ nʉtʉpɨtʉnʉ ton tʉtʉpɨ'se i'se te'to' awɨrɨ. 
\s1 Sises Ekoneka'pʉ Takon Non Kasa 
\p  
\v 5 Inserʉ amʉ' ena' orʉ tʉuye'ton nonkasa' iya pʉra iyesi, itesa' pe to' e'to' pe, usauro'nɨ na'ne'nokon ipɨ'.  
\v 6 E'tane, moro ipata esi mɨrɨ ka'pon uya ekamasa' na'ne' iyai rɨ: 
\q1 “Nai pan ka'pon ipɨ' ɨusewankama pa, 
\q2 mɨrɨ pe pʉra ka'pon mu imainanpa pa? 
\q1  
\v 7 Mara rʉ'kwɨ aiko pe ikoneka'pʉ auya inserʉ amʉ' o'no; 
\q2 arʉko'tɨ'pʉ auya eke pe iku'to' ike ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inamato' ike ke; 
\q2  
\v 8 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon nɨ nonka'pʉ auya i'ta o'koi',”\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Eren 8:4-6 (LXX)\f* 
\m tawon. Tanporon nɨ nonka tʉuya yau iyo'koi', Papa uya ɨ'rɨ rɨ nonkasa' pʉra iyesi innonka'pʉ pen itena'. Mɨrɨ rɨ e'tane, tanporon esa' pe ene pʉra rɨ iyesi.  
\v 9 E'tane Sises ene'nokon, mara rʉ'kwɨ aiko pe inserʉ amʉ' o'no ikonekasa' rʉ'pʉ, itarʉko'tɨsa' si a'kwa ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inamato' ke, apʉne pʉra uma'tan nɨto' yau iyekota'masa' pɨ', Papa uya wakʉ nonkasa' winɨ tanporon kon iwano' pe uma'tan nɨto' i'tuto' pe iya. 
\p  
\v 10 Wakʉ pe rɨ Papa esi'pʉ tu'kan kon tʉmunkɨ amʉ' nee'pʉ iya eke pe to' ku'to' ya', Sises rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ itiwano' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iporo tanporon nɨ uko'manto', uya to' epika'tɨto' esa' kuu'pʉ wakʉ pe iyenato' pe iyekota'ma winɨ.  
\v 11 Asa'rɨ rɨ kʉrɨ wakʉ pe ka'pon amʉ' konekanin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro wakʉ pe ikonekasa' kon esi tikin nɨ rɨ iyamʉtʉ pe. Mɨrɨ wenai, Sises ɨpiyɨtʉ pʉra iyesi takon non pe to' esakʉ tʉuya pɨ'. 
\q1  
\v 12 “Ɨyese' ekama uya mɨrɨ uyakon non pɨ'; 
\q2 iyamʉrasa' kon rau ayapurɨpɨtʉ pe userenka mɨrɨ,”\f + \fr 2:12 \ft Eren 22:22\f* 
\m ta iya.  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kanan, 
\q1 “Apurɨto' uya pe iyesi mɨrɨ.”\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Aisaya 8:17\f* 
\m Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ, 
\q1 “Serɨ yau e'ai', Papa nʉtʉrʉ'san mʉre amʉ' pokon pe,”\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Aisaya 8:18\f* 
\m takapʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 14 Kamoro si mʉre amʉ' esi pɨ' ka'pon amʉ' pe, tʉpun ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmʉnʉ ke, to' kaisa rɨ iyekoneka'pʉ, tʉuma'ta winɨ uma'tan nɨto' meruntɨrʉ esa' pe te'sen—Makoi—ma'tanʉ'to' pe tʉuya,  
\v 15 kamoro ita'sisa' pe te'san uma'tan nɨto' pɨ' enari'ke' pe tesi kon winɨ mo'ka pe.  
\v 16 I'nai rɨ sa'ne si iyesi inserʉ amʉ' pika'tɨ iya pen, e'tane Epʉra'an payan ton pika'tɨ iya.  
\v 17 Serɨ wenai takon non kasa iyekoneka'pʉ tanporon yau rɨ, ɨsentu'kena' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa Maimu awɨron pe use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin epuru pe te'to' pe, iyapiyo' pe tesi yau, ka'pon amʉ' konekanin pe ipokon pe to' makooi apai.\f + \fr 2:17 \fq ka'pon amʉ' konekanin pe ipokon pe to' makooi apai; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Papa uya kota'man nɨto' i'nɨ'panʉ'nin, umakooi kon mo'kanin.\f* 
\v 18 Apʉne pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ nɨrɨ ekota'ma'pʉ Makoi uya i'tupɨtʉ a'tai, kamoro nin si Makoi ni'tupɨtʉnʉ ton pika'tɨ iya mɨrɨ. 
\c 3  
\s1 Sises Eke, Mosi' Entaino 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', wakʉ ton utonpa ton, Papa nʉkɨ'ma'san, ɨusenuminkato' kon ikonekatɨ' Sises pɨ', itekare ekamai' enno'sa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin epuru, ina nekamanʉ.  
\v 2 Tanʉnnin pɨ' tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ iyesi'pʉ, Mosi' esi'pʉ kasa tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ tanporon yau Papa iwʉ' tau.\x - \xo 3:2 \xt Nonpa 12:7\x* 
\v 3 Sises i'tusa' esi'pʉ eke pe tʉnamasen pe Mosi' entai, ɨutɨ amɨnin uya tʉnamato' eporo kasa eke pe ɨutɨ nama entai.  
\v 4 Apʉne pʉra tanporo ɨutɨ ton amɨsa' mɨrɨ ka'pon uya, e'tane Papa esi tanporon nɨ amɨnin pe.  
\v 5 Mosi' esi'pʉ tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ ipoitorʉ pe tesi pɨ' tanporon yau Papa iwʉ' tau, ekama pɨ' serɨ enta' usauro'nɨto' ipɨ' pe te'sen.  
\v 6 E'tane Kʉrai esi tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ imu pe, Papa iwʉ' esa' pe. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ urɨ'nokon esi itiwʉ' pe, uta'sin nɨsa' pe iyesi yau enari'mʉra e'nɨto' pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ e'ku'nɨto' utapurɨn na'ne' ipɨ' pɨ'. 
\s1 Panaman Apurɨnin Pe Pʉra E'nɨ Namai' 
\p  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ si, Wakʉ A'kwarʉ nɨkayai'ne' kasa: 
\q1 “Serɨ pe, imaimu eta auya'nokon pe iyesi yau, 
\q2  
\v 8 ɨyewan kon kʉ'sa'mantanʉ'tʉu, 
\q1 ɨiwarɨ'nokon e'pai ɨwesi'pʉ kon kasa, 
\q2 ɨi'tuto' kon a'tai rɨmono' tau, 
\q1  
\v 9 ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon amʉ' uya ui'tupɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ui'tu i'se to' esi'pʉ na'ne' yau, 
\q2 mɨrɨpan kon uya unkupʉnʉ ene'pʉ 40 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya yau. 
\q1  
\v 10 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', mɨrɨ a'taino kon pɨ' usakorota'pʉ, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ, ‘Tʉutano'masen nɨ to' ewan, 
\q2 uyeseru i'tusa' to' uya pʉra rɨ iyesi,’ ta'pʉ uya. 
\q1  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ si, usakorotasa' yau usaurokʉ'pʉ kuru rɨ, 
\q2 ‘To' ewonto' oton pen nɨ umoronka'to' ya',’ ta'pʉ uya,”\f + \fr 3:11 \ft Eren 95:7-11 (LXX)\f* 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 12 Ti'tui' e'tɨ', utonpa ton, ɨri pe ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉse'nin, apurɨnin pe pʉra itewan tera'tɨsen pe Papa tʉuko'mansen piyapai.  
\v 13 E'tane wʉi kaisa rɨ ɨtonpa kon ipori'matɨ', “Serɨ pe,” tato' esi koro'tau, makoi uya enku'tɨn nɨto' uya asa'mantanʉkʉ kon namai'.  
\v 14 Kʉrai pokon pe enan nɨsa' serɨ uta'sin nɨsa' meruntɨ pe wapiya uyenu kon yau iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ pʉ'kʉ pona.  
\v 15 Serɨ pe kuru ta nesiine' kasa: 
\q1 “Serɨ pe imaimu eta auya'nokon pe iyesi yau, 
\q2 ɨyewan kon kʉ'sa'mantanʉ'tʉu 
\q1 ɨiwano' kon pe e'pai ɨwesi'pʉ kon a'taino kasa,”\f + \fr 3:15 \ft Eren 95:7-8 (LXX)\f* 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 16 Ɨnʉ' yan uya eta'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tiwano' kon pe e'pai to' ena'pʉ? Kamoro pen pe' Mosi' narɨ'san Isi' apai?  
\v 17 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' yan pɨ' isakorota'pʉ 40 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya? Kamoro pen pe' imakoitasa' kon rɨmono' tau, itekepu pe ita'po'sa' kon?  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' yan pɨ' Papa uya usaurokʉ'pʉ to' ewonto' oton pen pɨ' tʉumoronka'to' kon ya' ta? Kamoro pen pe' imaimu awɨron kon nʉ'san pen?\x - \xo 3:18 \xt Nonpa 14:1-35\x* 
\v 19 Mɨrɨ si ene'nokon to' ewomʉ poken pʉra iyesi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra to' uya apurɨ pʉra iyesi pɨ'. 
\c 4  
\s1 Sapa' Pɨ' Papa Munkɨ Amʉ' Umoronka'to' 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', moro rɨ marɨ isauro'sa' ipɨ' umoronka'nɨto' esi pɨ', ti'tuse e'nɨpai'nokon eporo poken pʉra auta'mo'kasa' kon esi namai'.  
\v 2 Urɨ'nokon nɨ nɨrɨ pɨ' itekare usekamasa' mɨrɨ, to' esi'pʉ na'ne' kasa; e'tane itekare to' neta'pʉ esi'pʉ ɨ'rɨ pe pʉra rɨ to' pona, apʉne pʉra kamoro etanin nʉ'san uya a'si'sa' pʉra iyesi'pʉ apurɨto' tʉuya'nokon pokon pe.  
\v 3 Serɨ pe nin si urɨ'nokon apurɨnin nʉ'san ewomʉ mɨrɨ umoronka'nɨto' ya', Papa uya tasa' na'ne' kasa, 
\q1 “Mɨrɨ si ekama'pʉ uya usakorota pe usaurokʉ yau, 
\q1 ‘To' ewonto' oton pen nɨ umoronka'to' ya',’”\f + \fr 4:3 \ft Eren 95:11; apʉne, v. 5 nɨrɨ enka'kɨ.\f* 
\m tawon. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itʉrawasooi rɨ u'ma'sa' e'tane non e'kaa'pʉ si'kɨrɨ.  
\v 4 Apʉne pʉra isauro'sa' mɨ airɨ rɨ 7 pe iku'nin wʉi pɨ' se ton main yau: “7 pe iku'nin wʉi yau Papa ereuta'pʉ tanporo tʉtʉrawasooi ton apai,”\f + \fr 4:4 \ft Iseneses 2:2 apʉne, v. 10 nɨrɨ enka'kɨ.\f* tukai'.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ na'ne' epoi te'sen yau ta iya, “To' ewonto' oton parɨ pen nɨ umoronka'to' ya',” ta. 
\p  
\v 6 Moro rɨ iyesi tʉron kon nɨ ewonto' oton mɨrɨ umoronka'nɨto' ya', kamoro ipana ya' itekare usekamasa' kon nʉ'san ewonsa' pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra main awɨrɨ pʉra to' esa' pɨ'.  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Papa uya kanan tʉron nɨ wʉi tʉka'sa', “Serɨ pe,” tato', emennʉ'pʉ kuru rɨ isaurokʉ'pʉ Tepi' poro, wapiya rɨ ta nesiine': 
\q1 “Serɨ pe, imaimu eta auya'nokon pe iyesi yau, 
\q2 ɨyewan kon kʉ'sa'mantanʉ'tʉu,”\f + \fr 4:7 \ft Eren 95:7-8 (LXX)\f* 
\m tukai'.  
\v 8 Apʉne pʉra Isa'suwa uya to' umoronka'to' pe to' ku'sa' yau, Papa nʉsauro'kapʉi'no pen kanan tʉron nɨ wʉi pɨ'.\x - \xo 4:8 \xt Isu'taronomi 31:7; Isa'suwa 22:4\x* 
\v 9 Moro rɨ iyesi Sapa' pɨ' umoronka'nɨto' Papa munkɨ amʉ' iwano';  
\v 10 apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ tewonsen Papa umoronka'to' ya' rɨ kanan umoronkapʉ mɨrɨ tiwano' tʉtʉrawasooi apai, tʉtʉrawasooi apai Papa esi'pʉ kasa.\x - \xo 4:10 \xt Iseneses 2:2\x* 
\v 11 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ewon nɨto' kon pe usi'tunpai'nokon kuru rɨ mɨrɨ umoronka'nɨto' ya', ɨnʉ' rɨ uta'mo'ka pe iyesi namai' Esuwerʉ amʉ' nʉkuu'pʉ main awɨrɨ pʉra te'se rɨmono' tau pɨkɨrɨ te'se. 
\p  
\v 12 Apʉne pʉra Papa maimu esi nurɨnan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iku'nin. Iyɨke' ɨsi'ratoi pokon iyɨ supara entaino, ewan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'kwarʉ rɨ i'monin, ɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ku'naai rɨ; ewan eseru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ usenuminkan nɨto' aimenkanin nɨ.  
\v 13 Ɨ'rɨ rɨ tanporo iye'ka'sa' yau na'ne' e'so'namʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi Papa enu apai. Tanporon nɨ e'nɨponkasa' mɨrɨpan esi kɨpo'po rɨ kʉrɨ usekaman nɨto' kuru rɨ ipɨ' enu yau. 
\s1 Sises, Eke Kuru Use'man Nɨto' Tʉrawasomanin Epuru 
\p  
\v 14 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', eke kuru si use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin epuru esa' pe e'nɨ pɨ', itɨsa' na'ne' Epʉn pona,\f + \fr 4:14 \fq Epʉn pona; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Epʉn awɨrɨ\f* Sises, Papa Mumu, uta'sinpai'nokon meruntɨ pe ekama na'ne' apurɨto' pɨ'.  
\v 15 Apʉne pʉra use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru upɨ'nokon ɨ'sɨ'mʉra e'nɨ pɨ' tʉusentu'masen pen pe pʉra te'sen esa' pe e'nɨ pɨ', e'tane urɨ'nokon kasa rɨ marɨ tanporon yau rɨ i'tupɨ'nɨto' yau iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ—e'tane rɨ imakoitasa' rʉ'pʉ pen.  
\v 16 Wakʉ nonkasa' na'ne' apon pona rɨken utɨnpai'nokon uyenu kon yau te'se, isentu'mato' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ nonkasa' iya epoto' pe upika'tɨnin kon pe upika'tɨnin kon i'se kuru e'nɨ a'tai. 
\c 5  
\p  
\v 1 Tanporon kon nɨ Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton esi anʉnsa' kon pe ka'pon amʉ' koro'tapai, mɨrɨpan esi anʉnsa' pe to' iwano' pe iku'nin pe Papa winɨkʉi' te'sen, to' nʉtʉrʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' use'mato' ike makoi esi pɨ'.  
\v 2 Ɨ'sɨ'mʉn yai esii'ma kamoro i'tu iya pʉra na'ne' nan koneka iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ nʉtano'mayai'ne' nan, apʉne pʉra tʉmɨrɨ esi pɨ' ɨ'sɨ'mʉra e'nɨto' yau.  
\v 3 Serɨ wenai tʉmakooi iwano' pe tʉuse'mato' tʉrʉ iya, ka'pon amʉ' makooi iwano' pe rɨ nɨrɨ itʉrʉ iya.\x - \xo 5:3 \xt Ripaiti'kas 9:7\x* 
\p  
\v 4 Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ serɨ itepuru pe e'nɨ namato' anʉmʉ pʉra iyesi tiwano' pe; Papa uya rɨken ikɨ'ma, Eran esi'pʉ kasa.\x - \xo 5:4 \xt E'sotas 28:1\x* 
\v 5 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, Kʉrai, tiwano' pe eke pe tʉku'to' ipɨ', Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru pe iyena'pʉ pen. E'tane Papa uya, 
\q1 “Umu ɨmɨrɨ tikin nan kuru rɨ; 
\q2 serɨ pe ɨkʉipʉnʉ pe enasa' serɨ,”\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Eren 2:7\f* 
\m ta'pʉ.  
\v 6 Tʉron nɨ airɨ, 
\q1 “Ɨmɨrɨ esi Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe inkero' pe rɨ, 
\q2 Merʉ'kisite' kasa kuru rɨ,”\f + \fr 5:6 \ft Eren 110:4\f* 
\m tasa' iya. 
\p  
\v 7 Sises uko'mamʉ a'tai non po, iyɨpʉremapɨtʉ'pʉ, isennapɨtʉ'pʉ eke pe tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'se, tenuku'mɨ tenno'se kʉrɨ, tʉpika'tɨnin pɨ' uma'tan nɨto' apai, mɨrɨpan maimu useta'pʉ apʉne pʉra iye'tʉsa' pɨ' Papa ena'.\x - \xo 5:7 \xt Ma'siu 26:36-46; Ma' 14:32-42; Ʉru' 22:39-46\x* 
\v 8 Imu pe rɨ iye'tane, main awɨron pe te'sen pe isenupa'pʉ tekota'mato' winɨ,  
\v 9 wakʉ pe nin si tekonekasa' ya', iyena'pʉ nin si inkero' pe rɨ epika'tɨn nɨto' pʉrakon pe tanporo tʉmaimu awɨron kon iwano' pe,  
\v 10 mɨrɨpan nin si ese'tɨ'pʉ Papa uya mɨrɨ, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru tukai', Merʉ'kisite' kasa kuru rɨ. 
\s1 Panaman Uta'mo'kan Namai' 
\p  
\v 11 Eke pe kuru ina usauro'to' man serɨ pɨ', e'tane ekama poken pʉra rɨ sa'man pe rɨ iyesi, apʉne pʉra tɨnɨn pɨ' rɨ tʉusenupasan pe ɨwesi kon.  
\v 12 Serɨ a'tai rɨ, ti'sa pe ɨyenasa' kon nesii'no, e'tane ɨyenupanin kon nɨ i'se ɨwesi kon iye'sara'tɨ si'kɨrɨ rɨ kanan Papa Maimu i'nairon pɨ'. Mana' rɨ marɨ i'se ɨwesi kon, sa'man kiyari pen!  
\v 13 Ɨnʉ' rɨ mana' pɨ' nʉko'manyai'ne', mʉre pe rɨ marɨ na'ne' esi mɨrɨ ipoken e'nɨto' pɨ' usenupan nɨto' to'ka'nʉ'sa' iya pʉra rɨ marɨ.\x - \xo 5:13 \xt 1 Koren 3:2\x* 
\v 14 E'tane sa'man kiyari esi mɨrɨ iyakʉ'pʉsa' kon iwano' pe, inke apurɨ tʉuya'nokon ke isenupasa' kon, wakʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri ka' se wa tawon nan pe. 
\c 6  
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', e'sara'tɨn pe Kʉrai pɨ' usenupan nʉ'pʉ tʉnɨnse, iyakʉ'pʉsa' pe e'nɨto' ya' utɨnpai'nokon, iyapon pe kanan era'tɨn nɨto' uma'tan nɨto' ya' anin nʉkupʉnʉ tʉka'pai'nokon pʉra,\f + \fr 6:1 \fq Uma'tan nɨto' ya' anin nʉkupʉnʉ tʉka'pai'nokon pʉra; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tʉwotori'pɨ kenan pen nɨ eseru apai\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa apurɨto',  
\v 2 epa'taisiman nɨto' pɨ' usenupan nɨto',\f + \fr 6:2 \fq epa'taisiman nɨto'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq ekorʉkan nʉkupʉnʉ.\f* miya' tʉto' pɨ', iyeri'sa' e'mʉ'sa'kato' pɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ siyaro' eseru aimenkato' nonkapai'nokon.  
\v 3 Iku'pai'nokon, Papa uya ta pe iyesi yau. 
\p  
\v 4 Iye'kupʉ poken pʉra iyesi kamoro a'kwa yau iye'sa' rʉ'san, Epʉn pon repan nɨto' onpanin nʉ'san, Wakʉ A'kwarʉ epoka'nin nʉ'san na'po to' uta'mo'kasa' tʉpo.  
\v 5 I'nai rɨ iyesi kamoro wakʉ Papa Maimu onpanin nʉ'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ enta' tʉuye'ton pana'pano.  
\v 6 Mɨrɨpan kon si uta'mo'kasa' pe iyesi yau, i'nai rɨ iyesi to' na'po pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra\f + \fr 6:6 \fq apʉne pʉra; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq koro'tau.\f* tʉma'tanʉ'nin kon pe to' uya kanan Papa Mumu pokapɨ'kapʉ kurusu' pona, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ annau to' uya ipiyɨ'nʉ'kapʉ rɨ marɨ. 
\p  
\v 7 Non inke rɨ tʉpona tʉuta'mo'kasen tuna ensinin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kiyari konekanin kamoro iyemaina'tɨsa' kon iwano' pe, uya Papa uya tʉpʉremato' eporo.  
\v 8 E'tane non, ɨmɨ'nɨ'ta mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'sini'ta a'tanʉ'nin esi mɨrɨ ɨri pe, ɨsɨ tʉpa'nʉ'se' yau. Iu'matʉ yau tepo'tɨ ton pe.\x - \xo 6:8 \xt Iseneses 3:17-18\x* 
\p  
\v 9 Serɨ kasa rɨ ina usauro'tane, utonpa ton amʉ' rʉ'kwɨ, ina enu yau rɨ wakʉ iwa ton esi ɨmɨrɨ'nokon pɨ'—wakʉ ton epika'tɨn nɨto' pɨkɨrɨ nʉye'ai'ne'.  
\v 10 Papa kʉrɨ rɨ ipoken pʉra iyesi ta pokena' pen nɨ ipɨ'; ɨtʉrawasooi kon nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'nʉnkato' auya'nokon ɨnenpoika'pʉ kon imunkɨ amʉ' pika'tɨ'pʉ auya'nokon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikupʉ pɨ' rɨ me'atʉi'ne' pu'tɨka'nʉkʉ iya pen nɨ.  
\v 11 Ina man akaisarɨ'nokon serɨ kuru kupʉ auya'nokon i'se ari'kena' pe iu'matʉ pona rɨ, ɨye'ku'to' kon konekanin pe i'nai rɨ.  
\v 12 Emiya'ne' pe ɨyena kon i'se pʉra ina man, e'tane kamoro apurɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuseta'kai' pʉra ipɨ' usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ eponin nʉ'san kasa e'tɨ'. 
\s1 I'nairon Papa Usauro'sa' Rʉ'pʉ Iku'to' Pe Tʉuya 
\p  
\v 13 Papa uya Epʉra'an auro'ka a'tai tʉnku'ton pɨ', tʉnesa'ton eke tentaino pʉra iyesi pɨ', tʉmɨrɨ pe rɨ iye'sesakʉ'pʉ,  
\v 14 “Urɨ pe kuru rɨ ɨpʉrema uya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tu'ke rɨ apayanʉ'tɨ uya,”\f + \fr 6:14 \ft Iseneses 22:16-17\f* tukai'.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ pɨ' si tʉuseta'kai' pʉra tenurikʉ tʉpo, Epʉra'an uya si iye'kupʉ tukai' tauro'kasa' rʉ'pʉ eporo'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 16 Ka'pon amʉ' uya tʉnkupʉnʉ kon ekama eke pe tentai'nokon te'san ese' yau, mɨrɨpan uya nin si isauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ meruntɨtanʉkʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan uya tanporon nɨ e'sei'pɨ'nɨto' ereutanʉkʉ.  
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra tʉnekama'pʉ usensima pʉra iyesi tukai' epoton kon uya i'tu i'se tesi wenai, tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ akonoma'pʉ iya ikupʉ uya kuru tukai'.  
\v 18 Papa uya serɨ kupʉ uya tasa', mɨrɨpan e'kupʉ kuru rɨ tasa' iya. Serɨ asa'ron usensima pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra kasi pe Papa esi poken pʉra iyesi. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', urɨ'nokon yainʉnsa' kon inota' e'se'na uya emenna' pe meruntɨ pe e'nɨto' anʉmʉ, apʉne pʉra uta'sin ke isauro'sa' pɨ' mɨrɨ itenu yau esii'ma.  
\v 19 Serɨ si e'ku'nɨto' esi uya'kwarʉ kon a'sinin pe, pana' pe, aka'ne' pe pen. Tewonsen siya rɨ iwapu enta',\x - \xo 6:19 \xt Ripaiti'kas 16:2\x* 
\v 20 Sises, ewomʉ'pʉ urawɨrɨ'nokon, uiwano' kon pe na'ne' ya'. Iyenasa' si Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru inkero' pe, Merʉ'kisite' kasa kuru rɨ.\x - \xo 6:20 \xt Eren 110:4\x* 
\c 7  
\s1 Merʉ'kisite', Papa Ena' Use'man Nɨto' Tʉrawasomanin 
\p  
\v 1 Pʉse rɨ Merʉ'kisite' esi'pʉ Seren po kin pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe, Eke Kuru Papa iwano' pe. Epʉra'an eporo'pʉ iya kin amʉ' ewa'noma tʉpo to' enu entai tenai' iyenna'po koro'tau, mɨrɨpan pʉrema'pʉ iya,  
\v 2 mɨrɨpan repa'pʉ Epʉra'an uya 1/10 kaisa rɨ tanporon apai. Itese' wapiya na'ne' esi mɨrɨ, “Ipoken te'sen kin,” ta e'kwa pe; “Seren pon kin,” ta esi kanan, “kin, tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨ esa',” ta e'kwa pe.\x - \xo 7:2 \xt Iseneses 14:17-20\x* 
\v 3 Kʉrɨ rɨ mu rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ pe pʉra kamoro imunkɨ rʉ'san ta poken pʉra rɨ iyesi Merʉ'kisite' pɨ', iweyu epiya'tɨ'pʉ pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ pe pʉra iko'manto' u'ma'sa' tato' pʉra rɨ iyesi, Papa Mumu kasa rɨ, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe moro rɨ iyesi inkero' pe rɨ. 
\p  
\v 4 Eke pe kuru rɨ iyesi'pʉ, tapai: Epʉra'an, utamokori kon uya irepa'pʉ 1/10 kaisa rɨ teyaton non enapai tʉnmo'ka'pʉ ke!  
\v 5 Main, Mosi' winon nin si esi Ripai payan use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe iyenasa' kon uya 1/10 kaisa rɨ to' uya amʉranʉ'to' pe ka'pon amʉ' piyapai—tʉtonpa kon amʉ' rɨ—Epʉra'an si'kɨrɨ rɨ to' u'tɨsa' e'tane.\x - \xo 7:5 \xt Nonpa 18:21\x* 
\v 6 Pʉse rɨ ka'pon uya Ripai pa pe te'to' e'ma'pʉkasa' pʉra rɨ iye'tane, mɨrɨ rɨ e'tane 1/10 kaisa rɨ Epʉra'an winɨ amʉranʉkʉ'pʉ iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipʉrema'pʉ iya, Papa uya tauro'kapɨ'sa' ton nʉ'pʉ esa' pe te'sen.  
\v 7 Ikasima pʉra, aiko pʉrema'pʉ eke pe te'sen uya.  
\v 8 Tikin nan esi 1/10 amʉranʉkʉ teri'san kon nɨ ka'pon amʉ' uya; e'tane tʉron nɨ pe kʉrɨ, nurɨne iyesi tato' uya amʉranʉkʉ.  
\v 9 Ka'pon uya rɨ ta poken iyesi, Ripai kʉrɨ rɨ 1/10 amʉranʉkʉ pɨ' na'ne' uya 1/10 e'ma'pʉ Epʉra'an poro,  
\v 10 apʉne pʉra Merʉ'kisite' uya Epʉra'an eposa' a'tai, Ripai esi'pʉ tʉtamokori pun yau rɨ marɨ. 
\s1 Sises, Merʉ'kisite' Waraino 
\p  
\v 11 Wakʉ pe ekonekan nɨto' e'seporo pe iyesi yau Ripai payan esi use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe koro'tau (mɨrɨ poro main e'tʉrʉ'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' ena'), ɨ'rɨto' pe ken si tʉron nɨ kanan use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin uyepʉ i'se e'nɨ'pʉ—Merʉ'kisite' waraino kuru, Eran waraino pen?  
\v 12 Apʉne pʉra si Eran poro use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin ye' pe te'sen usensimasa' a'tai, main nɨ nɨrɨ usensimato' pe iyesi.  
\v 13 Sises si, serɨ ton usauro'sa' na'ne' ipɨ' esi tʉponaron nɨ tʉron nɨ ko' rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨrɨ ko' awon nɨ e'tʉrawasomasa' pʉra iyesi use'man nɨto' apon po.  
\v 14 Apʉne pʉra i'tu rɨ uyepuru kon u'tɨsa' Isuta ko' winɨ, mɨrɨ ko' amʉ' pɨ' Mosi' usauro'sa' pʉra rɨ iyesi use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ina uya tasa' na'ne' esi wakʉ pe tenka'sen pe rɨ, tʉron nɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin Merʉ'kisite' waraino usenpoikasa' pe iyesi yau,  
\v 16 kʉrɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe iyenasa' main winɨ itamokori ton e'sa' wenai pen, e'tane tu'ma'sen pen uko'man nɨto' meruntɨrʉ winɨ.  
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra isekamasa': 
\q1 “Ɨmɨrɨ esi use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe inke rɨ, 
\q2 Merʉ'kisite' kasa kuru rɨ,”\f + \fr 7:17 \ft Eren 110:4\f* 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 18 Wapiyaro' main, Mosi' winon utamasa' apʉne pʉra ɨ'sɨ'mʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pika'tɨnin pe pʉra iyesi pɨ'  
\v 19 (apʉne pʉra main uya ɨ'rɨ konekasa' pʉra iyesi wakʉ pe), mɨrɨpan wakʉ parɨ nin si e'ku'nɨto' ekamasa', a'ko pe nin si Papa piya' une'nin kon. 
\p  
\v 20 Iye'ku'to' pe ikupʉ uya ta Papa uya a'kɨrɨ iyekonekasa'! Tʉron kon use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan ekonepɨtʉ'pʉ iye'ku'to' pe ikupʉ uya ta Papa uya a'kɨrɨ pʉra.  
\v 21 E'tane Sises ekoneka'pʉ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe iye'ku'to' pe ikupʉ uya ta Papa uya a'kɨrɨ, ta'pʉ iya ipɨ' a'tai: 
\q1 “Itepuru uya iye'ku'to' pe ikupʉ uya tasa', 
\q2 mɨrɨpan uya teseru ensima pen: 
\q1 ‘Ɨmɨrɨ esi use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe inke rɨ.’”\f + \fr 7:21 \ft Eren 110:4\f* 
\m tasa' iya.  
\v 22 Apʉne pʉra serɨ tasa' pɨ', Sises ekonekasa' wakʉ kuru nin ekonekan nɨsa' wapiyaro' entaino ekamanin pe. 
\p  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ si, tu'ke rɨ kamoro use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan esi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra uma'tan nɨto' uya to' uko'mamʉ tʉtʉrawasooi kon kupʉ pɨ' poken pʉra ikupʉ wenai;  
\v 24 e'tane si, Sises uko'mamʉ pɨ' inke rɨ, aka'nero' pe pʉra nin si use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin ye' pe iyesi.  
\v 25 Mɨrɨ pe nin si iyesi pɨ', kamoro Papa piya' tʉuye'san tʉporo pika'tɨ iya mɨrɨ tenuka'nʉ'se kuru,\f + \fr 7:25 \fq tenuka'nʉ'se kuru; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tɨwɨro' pe\f* apʉne pʉra tɨwɨrɨ rɨ tʉuko'mamʉ pɨ' to' pona usennan pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 26 Pʉse rɨ warai nin si use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya i'se e'nɨto' eporo mɨrɨ—kʉrɨ wakʉ pe na'ne', ɨ'rɨ ɨri pʉn nɨ, esukenan nɨ, tʉmakooikena' nan piyapai iyemo'kasa', ka' enta' rɨ iyenu'sa'.  
\v 27 Tʉron kon use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton kasa pʉra iyesi, wʉi kaisarɨ rɨ use'man nɨto' ton tʉrawasomato' iya pʉra iyesi, wapiya tʉmakooi iwano' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka'pon amʉ' makooi iwano' pe. To' makooi iwano' pe iye'tʉrʉ'pʉ tikin ite'kwa tʉnakonomaton pe pʉra rɨ tʉmɨrɨ pe use'man nɨto' ike pe.\x - \xo 7:27 \xt Ripaiti'kas 9:7\x* 
\v 28 Main uya ɨ'sɨ'mʉnon ka'pon amʉ' anʉmʉ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton pe; e'tane iye'to' pe tawon, iye'sa' na'ne' main ekoneka'pʉ tʉpo, uya Imu anʉmʉ'pʉ, iyekonekasa' wakʉ pe inkero' pe. 
\c 8  
\s1 Sises, Emenna' Ekonekan Nɨto' Epuru 
\p  
\v 1 Se kuru sa'ne ta ina uya: Pʉse rɨ warai use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru esa' pe e'nɨ, iyereutasa' rʉ'pʉ enwo'ne' miya' winɨ eke pe kuru te'sen ye' apon po Epʉn po,\x - \xo 8:1 \xt Eren 110:1\x* 
\v 2 te'tʉrawasomasen ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' tau, i'nairon kuru ta'porin, Itepuru rɨ ni'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, ka'pon ni'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ pen. 
\p  
\v 3 Tanporon kon use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru pe anʉnsa' uya asa'rɨ rɨ tʉtʉsen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ use'man nɨto' ike tʉrʉ, mɨrɨ kasa rɨ si pʉse rɨ nʉtʉton nɨ marɨ esi'pʉ.  
\v 4 Non po iyesi yau, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin pe pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra moro ka'pon amʉ' esi pɨ' tʉtʉsen tʉnin nan pe main uya ekamasa' awɨrɨ.  
\v 5 To' e'tʉrawasoma Epʉn pon ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' a'kwarʉ'pʉ tau rɨ, ikasa ipatakasa' pe te'sen. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Mosi' panama'pʉ mɨrɨ ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' amɨ pɨ' iyekoneka koro'tau: “Menei', tanporon nɨ koneka auya, ɨyena' wʉ' po enpoika'pʉ na'ne' kasa ento' auya ipɨ' pe,”\f + \fr 8:5 \ft E'sotas 25:40\f* tukai'.  
\v 6 E'tane Sises tʉrawasooi ineporo'pʉ esi eke pe Mosi' tʉrawasooi entai, wakʉ kuru ekonekan nɨsa' Papa winon eposa' iya tʉntʉton eke pe penaro' entai, mɨrɨpan e'tʉsa' wakʉ ton kuru nin e'ku'to' pɨ' isauro'sa' po. 
\p  
\v 7 Apʉne pʉra wapiyaro' ekonekan nɨto' esi yau wakʉ pe, tʉron nɨ ne'warinpai'no pen nɨ.  
\v 8 E'tane Papa uya ɨri eporo'pʉ tʉmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ', mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ, 
\q1 “Iweyu uye'nɨ pɨ' man, ta pɨ' Itepuru man, 
\q2 emenna' ekonekan nɨto' konekato' uya weyu 
\q1 Esuwerʉ amʉ' pokon pe, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isuta amʉ' pokon pe. 
\q1  
\v 9 To' tamokori ton pokon pe unkoneka'pʉ 
\q2 ekonekan nɨto' waraino pen, 
\q1 to' emiya pɨ' to' a'si'pʉ uya a'taino 
\q2 to' ato' pe uya Isi' apai, 
\q1 apʉne pʉra tʉmɨrɨ'nokon pokon pe ekoneka a'tai tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ kon awɨrɨ pʉra to' esi'pʉ, 
\q2 mɨrɨpan kon piyapai era'tɨ'pʉ, 
\qr ta Itepuru uya. 
\q1  
\v 10 Se si serɨ ekonekan nɨto' konekato' uya Esuwerʉ amʉ' pokon pe, 
\q2 mɨrɨ pata'pʉ pe, ta Itepuru uya, 
\q1 Umaimu nonka uya mɨrɨ to' usenuminkato' ya' 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imenuka uya to' ewan pɨ'. 
\q1 To' e'to' itese' pɨ' pe e'to' oton, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umunkɨ amʉ' pe to' e'to' oton. 
\q1  
\v 11 Serɨ enta' ka'pon uya tʉtonpa enupato' oton pen, 
\q2 mɨrɨ pe pʉra ka'pon uya takon enupato' oton pen, ‘Itepuru i'tukɨ,’ tukai', 
\q1 apʉne pʉra tanporo to' uya ui'tuto' oton 
\q2 sepan kon apai eke ton pe kuru te'san pona rɨ. 
\q1  
\v 12 Ɨri to' eseru pɨ' usentu'mato' oton, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uyenu yau to' makooi ku'to' uya oton pen nɨ mɨrɨ enta',”\f + \fr 8:12 \ft Iseremaya 31:31-34 (LXX)\f* 
\m tasa'. 
\p  
\v 13 Serɨ si ekonekan nɨto' esakʉ iya winɨ “emenna',” tukai', wapiyaro' ku'sa' iya tapurɨsen pe pʉra; mɨrɨpan si tapurɨsen pe pʉra te'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipooi'pɨ pe te'sen pʉra iyena serɨ pe rɨ. \fig To' e'tʉrawasoma Epʉn pon ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' a'kwarʉ'pʉ tau rɨ, ikasa ipatakasa' pe te'sen.|src="CN01921B.tif" size="span" loc="HEB 8:1-13" copy="David C. Cook" ref="8:5" \fig* 
\c 9  
\s1 Apurɨpɨtʉ, Non Pon Ta'porin Tau 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ si wapiyaro' ekonekan nɨto' esi'pʉ, teseru ke Papa apurɨpɨ'to' esi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' serɨ non pon kanan.  
\v 2 Ta'porin i'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ. Wapiyaro' iwa'kʉ'sa' tau raan'pu apon esi'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tepʉrʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipʉremasa' pʉreti; serɨ esakʉ mɨrɨ Wakʉ Pata, tukai'.\x - \xo 9:2 \xt E'sotas 26:1-30; 25:31-40, 23-30\x* 
\v 3 Isakon pe te'sen iwapu entau iwa'kʉ'sa' kanan esakʉ esi'pʉ Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata, tukai',\x - \xo 9:3 \xt E'sotas 26:31-33\x* 
\v 4 mɨrɨ yau korʉ pun konekasa' use'man nɨto' apon a'po'nan kɨrɨi'nʉnpato' ipo, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ korʉ ke ipi'pɨ'tɨsa' ekonekan nɨsa' en. Serɨ yau kanan korʉ pun konekasa' samaku pe yau “mana” tato' to' yu pe iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ esi'pʉ, Eran yʉʉi iyenpʉrʉkʉtasa' rʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨ' amʉ' ekonekan nɨto' apon ton.\x - \xo 9:4 \xt E'sotas 30:1-6; 25:10-16; 16:33; Nonpa 17:8-10; E'sotas 25:16; Isu'taronomi 10:3-5\x* 
\v 5 Mɨrɨ iten pʉro'po ika'sa' ton inserʉ amʉ' A'kwa iwano' ton esi'pʉ, ɨri pe e'nɨ'pʉ apai ekonekan pata'se' epoino.\f + \fr 9:5 \fq ekonekan pata'se' epoino; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq pɨ' wannɨ usentu'man apon.\f* E'tane serɨ ton ekama poken pʉra man tanporo serɨ pe.\x - \xo 9:5 \xt E'sotas 25:18-22\x*\fig korʉ ke ipi'pɨ'tɨsa' ekonekan nɨsa' en|src="CN02092B.tif" size="col" loc="HEB 9:1-5" copy="David C. Cook" ref="9:4" \fig* 
\p  
\v 6 Serɨ kasa si ikonekasa' ya', use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan ewomʉ ɨsi'pakɨrɨ rɨ kɨpo'pon iwa iwa'kʉ'sa' ta' tʉtʉrawasooi kon ku'se'na.\x - \xo 9:6 \xt Nonpa 18:2-6\x* 
\v 7 E'tane use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru rɨken ewomʉ i'nawon iwa'kʉ'sa' ta' tikin ite'kwa rɨken wʉipiya yau, mʉn esa' pe kuru itɨto' pe iyesi tʉntʉton pe tʉmakooi epe'pʉ pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka'pon amʉ' makooi epe'pʉ pe to' nʉkupʉ'pʉ i'tui'ma pʉra rɨ.\x - \xo 9:7 \xt Ripaiti'kas 16:2-34\x* 
\v 8 Wakʉ A'kwarʉ uya enpoika'pʉ serɨ winɨ Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata e'ma uta'kokasa' pʉra iyesi moro rɨ marɨ wapiyaro' tʉponaron iponaro' ta'porin esi pɨ'.  
\v 9 Serɨ serɨ, serɨ a'taino ekamanin, tʉtʉsen, use'man nɨto' ike itʉsa' rʉ'pʉ uya apurɨpɨ'nin nan ewan konekasa' pʉra iyesi.  
\v 10 Kiyari pe rɨ nin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tensisen pe rɨ nin iyesi'pʉ, ekorʉkan pe rɨ—kɨpo'pon eseru pe rɨ nin emenna' eseru weyu e'seporo pona rɨ. 
\s1 Kʉrai Mʉnʉ 
\p  
\v 11 Kʉrai uye'sa' a'tai use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru pe wakʉ ton serɨ yau iyenaka'sa' na'ne' ton\f + \fr 9:11 \fq iyenaka'sa' na'ne' ton; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq serɨ ya' tʉuye'ton.\f* iwano' pe, itɨ'pʉ eke kuru ipan pe wakʉ pe te'sen ta'porin ka'pon nʉkoneka'pʉ pen awɨrɨ, serɨ rɨ ika'sa' pʉ'kʉ ta pen sa'ne.  
\v 12 Kapirita mʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ paka mʉre mʉnʉ winɨ iyewomʉ'pʉ pen; e'tane iyewomʉ'pʉ Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata ya' tikin ite'kwa tʉnakonomaton pe pʉra rɨ tʉmʉnʉ winɨ rɨ, tɨwɨro' pe rɨ uye'mato' kon tepose.  
\v 13 Kapirita amʉ' mʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ warawo' pe te'sen paka amʉ' mʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ paka mʉre po'tɨsa' urumɨrʉ'pʉʉi tʉrʉ'pɨ'sa' kamoro ɨri pe te'san\f + \fr 9:13 \fq ɨri pe te'san; \ft ike'ike pe te'san kasa te'san\f* korʉkanin pe ɨri apai to' e'to' pe wakʉ pe kɨpo'po.\x - \xo 9:13 \xt Ripaiti'kas 16:15-16; Nonpa 19:9, 17-19\x* 
\v 14 Mɨrɨ entai kuru rɨ nin si Kʉrai mʉnʉ, aka'nero' pen Iya'kwarʉ awɨrɨ iye'tʉsa' rʉ'pʉ tiwano' pe tʉmaku'pɨ ke pʉra Papa ena', uya uyewan kon korʉka, unkupʉnʉ kon uyanin kon uma'tan nɨto' ya' apai,\f + \fr 9:14 \fq Uma'tan nɨto' ya' apai; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq ɨ'rɨ ku'nin pen nɨ iku'to' pe iku'sa' apai.\f* Papa nurɨnan apiyo' pe e'nɨto' pe! 
\p  
\v 15 Serɨ wenai Kʉrai esi emenna' ekonekan nɨto' yau iporo e'nɨto' pe, kamoro si ikɨ'masa' kon uya iye'kupʉ tukai' auro'kasa' kon uya tʉtʉsen epoto' pe siyaro' rɨ—serɨ si tʉuma'tasa' pɨ' to' epe' pe to' mo'kanin pe makoi, to' nʉkupʉ'pʉ apai wapiyaro' ekonekan nɨto' o'noro esii'ma. 
\p  
\v 16 Eri'nɨsa' a'tai te'nonkasen imamin nʉ'pʉ wannɨ karetaai esi a'tai, i'nai rɨ pe' inonka tawon nʉ'pʉ eri'kaa'pʉ tukai' ti'tusen pe iyesi,  
\v 17 apʉne pʉra inonkasa' anʉnto' pe iyesi, tawon nʉ'pʉ erikʉ'pʉ a'tai rɨken; nurɨne tawon nʉ'pʉ e'tane pʉra.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ wenai wapiyaro' ekonekan nɨto' e'kupʉ pʉra iye'pɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ mʉn e'kwansa' pʉra iye'tane.  
\v 19 Mosi' uya tanporon nɨ apiyontɨn nɨto' main yau na'ne' ekama a'tai tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' pana ya', paka munkɨ mʉnʉ anʉmʉ'pʉ iya tuna amʉtʉ pe, tʉtariren karimeru i'po' konekasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'so'pu ye' tato' panta, mɨrɨpan uya kareta amon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' pai'pai'ma'pʉ ike.  
\v 20 “Serɨ serɨ ekonekan nɨto' mʉnʉ, Papa uya ayapiyontɨsa' kon na'ne' iyawɨrɨ ɨwesi kon pa,”\f + \fr 9:20 \ft E'sotas 24:8\f* ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, ta'porin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itau tapurɨsen ɨ'rɨ e'kupʉ yau pai'pai'ma'pʉ iya mʉn ke.\x - \xo 9:21 \xt Ripaiti'kas 8:15\x* 
\v 22 I'nai rɨ sa'ne main esi tanporon iwa rɨ ekorʉka i'se mʉn ke, apʉne pʉra mʉn utɨsa' pʉra iye'tane makoi pɨ' usentu'man pʉra rɨ iyesi.\x - \xo 9:22 \xt Ripaiti'kas 17:11\x* 
\p  
\v 23 Iye'ku'to' pe kuru iyesi'pʉ Epʉn pon patakanin ekorʉkato' pe iyesi'pʉ serɨ ton use'man nɨto' ton ike mʉnʉ ke, e'tane si Epʉn po'nan kuru nin si ekorʉkato' pe iyesi serɨ entaino use'man nɨto' ton ike ke.  
\v 24 Apʉne pʉra Kʉrai ewonsa' pʉra iyesi Epʉn pon patakanin ka'pon nʉkoneka'pʉ ɨpʉreman pata'se' ya' i'nairon patakanin ya'; Epʉn pona kuru rɨ nin iyepa'ka'pʉ, serɨ pe si tʉusenpoika ton pe urɨ'nokon iwano' pe Papa piya'.  
\v 25 Mɨrɨ pe pʉra Epʉn pona iyepa'ka'pʉ e'tʉpɨ'se'na kanan pen, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru kasa Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata ya' wʉipiya kaisa rɨ tʉmʉnʉ pen nɨ esa' pe.  
\v 26 Kʉrai rɨ nin uya e'ne' moronka nesii'no inke rɨ, non e'kaa'pʉ si'kɨrɨ rɨ. E'tane si isenpoikasa' tikin ite'kwa tʉnakonomaton pe pʉra rɨ nin, pata weyu u'matʉ a'tai makoi eno'ma pe tʉmɨrɨ ke tʉuse'ma ke.  
\v 27 Ka'pon erikʉ tikin ite'kwa na'ne' kasa, mɨrɨ tʉpo eseru aimenkato' epoton pe,  
\v 28 mɨrɨ kasa si Kʉrai e'tʉrʉ'pʉ tikin ite'kwa tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' makooi mo'kanin pe; mɨrɨpan usenpoikato' oton iyakon ite'kwa pe, makoi tʉrawasomase'na pen, e'tane epika'tɨn nɨto' ne'se'na kamoro tenupɨkɨrɨ te'san iwano' pe.\x - \xo 9:28 \xt Aisaya 53:12\x* 
\c 10  
\s1 Kʉrai E'tʉrʉ'pʉ Use'man Nɨto' Ike Pe Tikin Ite'kwa Rɨ 
\p  
\v 1 Main, Mosi' winon esi wakʉ ton tʉuye'sen a'kwarʉ'pʉ pe rɨ—tʉuye'ton kapisin pe iyesi. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', kamoro a'ko pe Papa apurɨpɨ'se tʉuye'san koneka iya pʉra iyesi wakʉ pe, mɨrɨ rɨ use'man nɨto' ike utakonomapɨ'tane wʉipiya kaisarɨ rɨ.  
\v 2 To' konekanin pe iyesi yau, use'man nɨto' ike ereuta'pʉ nesii'no. Papa apurɨpɨ'nin nan ekorʉka'pʉ nesii'no tikin nan parɨ rɨ, tʉmakooi ke to' nʉsi'tui'no pen nɨ.  
\v 3 E'tane nin si mɨrɨ use'man nɨto' esi wʉipiya kaisa rɨ makoi pɨ' emiya'pontɨpɨ'nin pe,  
\v 4 apʉne pʉra paka, warawo' pe te'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kapirita mʉnʉ uya makoi mo'ka pʉra rɨ iyesi ke. 
\p  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', tʉuyepʉ a'tai serɨ non pona, Kʉrai uya ta'pʉ: 
\q1 “Use'man nɨto' ike mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtʉsen i'se pʉra ɨwesi'pʉ, 
\q2 e'tane upun ɨnkoneka'pʉ; 
\q1  
\v 6 ɨyepori'ma pʉra iyesi'pʉ 
\q2 ipo'tɨ pe tʉtʉsen pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi ku'sa' epe'pʉ pe tʉtʉsen pɨ'. 
\q1  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ a'tai ta'pʉ uya, ‘Moro rɨ e'ai', 
\q2 Papa, uye'sa' man i'se ɨwe'to' ku'se'na—iye'menukasa' na'ne' kasa upɨ' kareta amon pɨ',’”\f + \fr 10:7 \ft Eren 40:6-8 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 8 Ta'pʉ iya wapiya, “Use'man nɨto' ike mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtʉsen, ipo'tɨ pe tʉtʉsen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi ku'sa' epe'pʉ pe tʉtʉsen i'se pʉra ɨwesi'pʉ, pori' pe pʉra ɨwesi'pʉ ipɨ',” ta'pʉ iya (main uya rɨ iye'ku'to' pe tasa' e'tane).  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ a'tai, “Moro rɨ e'ai', uye'sa' man i'se ɨwe'to' ku'se'na,” ta'pʉ iya. Wapiyaro' use'man nɨto' wʉrʉuka'pʉ iya ipɨkɨron pata pe.  
\v 10 Mɨrɨ si i'se iye'to' winɨ, wakʉ pe nin si ekonekan nɨsa'nokon, Sises Kʉrai pun use'man nɨto' ike poro tikin nan parɨ rɨ. 
\p  
\v 11 Wʉi kaisarɨ rɨ tanporon kon use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan e'soto'kasa' uya tʉtʉrawasooi kon kupʉ; mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ akonomapɨtʉ pɨ', makoi mo'kanin pen nɨ.\x - \xo 10:11 \xt E'sotas 29:38\x* 
\v 12 E'tane nin pʉse rɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin uya tikin ite'kwa rɨ use'man nɨto' makoi iwano' pe tʉrʉ'pʉ siyaro' pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan nin si ereutasa' Papa emiyatʉ enwo'netʉ winɨ.\x - \xo 10:12 \xt Eren 110:1\x* 
\v 13 Mɨrɨ si'kɨrɨ, iyenurikʉ si ti'ta apon pe teyaton non koneka enupɨkɨrɨ,  
\v 14 apʉne pʉra tikin nan nɨ use'man nɨto' ike ke kamoro wakʉ pe tekonekasan konekasa' iya wakʉ pe inkero' pe rɨ. \fig Ɨyepori'ma pʉra iyesi'pʉ ipo'tɨ pe tʉtʉsen pɨ'.|src="CN02093B.tif" size="col" loc="HEB 10:1-14" copy="David C. Cook" ref="10:6" \fig* 
\p  
\v 15 Wakʉ A'kwarʉ uya rɨ nɨrɨ serɨ ekamasa' upɨ'nokon. Ta iya wapiya: 
\q1  
\v 16 “Serɨ serɨ to' pokon pe ekonekato' 
\q2 mɨrɨ tʉpo, ta Itepuru uya. 
\q1 Main uiwano' emaika uya to' ewan ya', 
\q2 to' usenuminkato' pɨ' imenuka uya.”\f + \fr 10:16 \ft Iseremaya 31:33\f* 
\m  
\v 17 Mɨrɨpan pirikʉ iya: 
\q1 “To' makooi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ main uya tato' awɨrɨ pʉra to' nʉkupʉnʉ 
\q2 kupʉ uya pen uyenu yau,”\f + \fr 10:17 \ft Iseremaya 31:34\f* 
\m ta iya.  
\v 18 Serɨ ton pɨ' si usentu'man nɨsa' pɨ', makoi ku'sa' pɨ' use'man nɨto' pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ. 
\s1 A'ko Pe Papa Piya' Uye'nɨpai'nokon 
\p  
\v 19 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', utonpa ton, ewon nɨ'nokon Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata ya' tukai' uyenu kon yau e'nɨ'nokon pɨ' Sises mʉnʉ winɨ,  
\v 20 emenna' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ nurɨnan uye'ma kon uta'kokasa' pɨ' iwapu awɨrɨ, ipun nɨ si,  
\v 21 eke si use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin esi pɨ' Papa iwʉ' esa' pe,  
\v 22 uye'nɨpai'nokon si a'ko pe Papa piya' wakʉ pe itewan, apurɨto' esa' pe uyewan kon yau, iyepai'pai'masa' ukorʉkanin kon pe ɨri ku'nin nʉ'pʉ pe usi'tun nɨto' apai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ upun kon iyekorʉkasa' pe esukenan tuna ke.\x - \xo 10:22 \xt Ripaiti'kas 8:30; Isi'kiyerʉ 36:25\x* 
\v 23 Uta'sinpai'nokon pana' pe e'ku'nɨto' unekamanʉ kon pɨ', apʉne pʉra isauro'sa' rɨ esi tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨron pe rɨ.  
\v 24 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ utonpa kon pɨ' tʉusenuminkasen pe e'nɨpai'nokon to' pori'manin pe tʉusi'nʉnkasen pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ku'nin pe to' e'to' pe.  
\v 25 Amʉrapɨ'nɨto' eseru nonkapai'nokon pʉra, tʉron kon nʉnonkayai'ne' kasa, e'tane utonpa kon pori'mapɨ'pai'nokon—miyarɨ parɨ apʉne pʉra Iweyu e'seporo enkapʉ auya'nokon pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 26 Ipɨ' rɨ te'ku'se umakoitan pɨ' uko'man nɨ yau i'nairon anʉnkapʉ tʉpo, mɨrɨ rupɨ makoi iwano' pe use'man nɨto' e'ku'sa' pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ,  
\v 27 e'tane enari'nʉn nɨto' rɨken eseru aimenkato' e'seporo pɨ', ɨsɨ rɨ apo', Papa eyaton non po'tɨ ton.\x - \xo 10:27 \xt Aisaya 26:11 (LXX)\x* 
\v 28 Ɨnʉ' rɨ Mosi' winon main awɨron pen wɨpɨtʉ'pʉ usentu'man pʉra rɨ ipɨ', asa'ron kon mɨrɨ pe pʉra osorʉwawon kon uya tʉnene'pʉ kon ɨri kupʉ iya ekamasa' pɨ'.\x - \xo 10:28 \xt Isu'taronomi 17:6; 19:15\x* 
\v 29 Ɨ'rɨ kaisa rɨ ken si ka'pon kota'mato' pe iyesi, Papa Mumu wasa'pɨ'nin ti'ta ke, sepan pe rɨ tʉkonekanin pe te'sen ekonekan nɨto' mʉnʉ ku'nin, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ nonkasa' Iya'kwarʉ uya sapemanin nʉ'pʉ tukai', mi'tuyatʉu?\x - \xo 10:29 \xt E'sotas 24:8\x* 
\v 30 I'tu'nokon serɨ tawon nʉ'pʉ, “Urɨ rɨ e'manin; urɨ uya ina'po,”\f + \fr 10:30 \ft Isu'taronomi 32:35\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kanan, “Itepuru uya tʉmunkɨ amʉ' eseru aimenka.”\f + \fr 10:30 \ft Isu'taronomi 32:36; Eren 135:14\f* 
\v 31 Ɨsɨ pe rɨ iyesi Papa nurɨnan ena' uta'mo'kan. 
\p  
\v 32 Ɨyenu kon yau nesii iweyu anʉnsa' auya'nokon a'taino rʉ'pʉ, meruntɨ pe ɨye'soto'ka'pʉ kon eke rɨ sa'man usi'tun nɨto' annawɨrɨ rɨ.  
\v 33 Tʉron nɨ a'tai annau rɨ asapemapɨtʉ'pʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ pe rɨ ɨkota'ma'pʉ kon; tʉron nɨ a'tai kamoro mɨrɨ kasa tʉku'san pokon pe rɨ ɨye'soto'pɨtʉ'pʉ kon.  
\v 34 Kamoro pariki'si tau te'san pɨ' ɨusentu'mapɨtʉ'pʉ kon, ɨimamin kon nɨ mo'kasa' e'tane pori' pe rɨ ɨwesi'pʉ kon, apʉne pʉra i'tu auya'nokon ke wakʉ parɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inke tʉuko'mansen ɨiwano' kon esi pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 35 Mɨrɨ pɨ' ɨyenu kon yau ɨwe'to' kon kʉseno'matʉu; eke pe ɨyepe'pʉ kon eporo auya'nokon mɨrɨ.  
\v 36 Sa'man annawɨrɨ rɨ ɨutɨto' kon pe iyesi te'nonkai' pʉra, Papa e'to' i'se ku'sa' auya'nokon a'tai, isaurokʉ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ iye'ku'to' pe eporo kon pa.  
\v 37 Apʉne pʉra serɨ pe iwa'ne rɨ, 
\q1 “Tʉuye'sen uye'nɨ pɨ' man, emennʉ'pʉ iyepʉ pen. 
\q2  
\v 38 E'tane ipokena' e' pe te'sen uko'mamʉ mɨrɨ apurɨto' winɨ. 
\q1 Tesi'pʉ ya' iyenna'posa' yau, 
\q2 pori' pe ipɨ' esi pen mɨrɨ,”\f + \fr 10:38 \ft Apa'ka' 2:3-4 (LXX)\f* 
\m tasa' iya.  
\v 39 E'tane urɨ'nokon kamoro to' kasa tenna'posan pen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuma'tasan pen, e'tane kamoro apurɨnin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tepika'tɨsan iye'ton pe te'san. 
\c 11  
\s1 Apurɨto' Iwinɨ 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ si apurɨto' esi mɨrɨ i'nai rɨ iyesi tato' e'ku'nɨto' pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ moro kuru iyesi tato' entane pʉra rɨ.  
\v 2 Serɨ pɨ' penaro' kon apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 3 Apurɨto' winɨ ito'ka'nʉkʉ tanporo non ekoneka'pʉ Papa maimu ke, tensen pe na'ne' ekoneka'pʉ tensen pen apai.\x - \xo 11:3 \xt Iseneses 1:1; Eren 33:6, 9; Isaan 1:3\x* 
\v 4 Apurɨto' winɨ Eperʉ uya wakʉ tʉuse'mato' tʉrʉ'pʉ Papa ena' wakʉ Keen nʉtʉrʉnʉ entaino. Apurɨto' winɨ apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ ipokena' e' pe te'sen tukai', Papa usauro'sa' a'tai wakʉ pe intʉrʉnʉ ton pɨ'. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apurɨto' winɨ isaurokʉ rɨ, teri'sa' rɨ e'tane.\x - \xo 11:4 \xt Iseneses 4:3-10\x* 
\p  
\v 5 Apurɨto' winɨ Iino' enuku'pʉ serɨ yau uko'man nɨto' apai, eri'nɨto' i'tu tʉuya namai'; iye'seporo pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra Papa uya anʉmʉ'pʉ. Apʉne pʉra itanʉmʉ rawɨrɨ, apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ pori' pe Papa ku'nin tukai'.\x - \xo 11:5 \xt Iseneses 5:21-24 (LXX)\x* 
\v 6 Apurɨto' pʉra iye'tane pori' pe Papa kupʉ auya pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ ipiya' tʉuye'sen uya apurɨto' pe kuru iyesi moro iyesi tukai', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'nai rɨ tʉwarinpanin nan e'ma iya tukai'. 
\p  
\v 7 Apurɨto' winɨ Nowa esi'pʉ, tʉpanama a'tai tʉusensen pen nɨ pɨ', Papa nama tʉuya pɨ' a' kaa'pʉ iya tamʉtʉ pokon pe tepika'tɨto' yau. Iko'manto' winɨ apurɨto' yau non pon kon eno'ma'pʉ iya, e'tane Papa uya tanʉmʉ kuu'pʉ iya ipokena' pe e'nɨto' anʉnnin pe apurɨto' iya winɨ.\x - \xo 11:7 \xt Iseneses 6:13-22\x* 
\p  
\v 8 Apurɨto' winɨ Epʉra'an, tʉkɨ'masa' a'tai tʉutɨto' pe pata tʉpata'se' pe itʉton ya', uya apurɨ'pʉ mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨ ya' utɨ tukai' i'tui'ma pʉra rɨ.\x - \xo 11:8 \xt Iseneses 12:1-5\x* 
\v 9 Apurɨto' winɨ tʉpata oton koneka'pʉ iya usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' nono yau, ka'kʉran pe rɨ ɨnnon nɨ pata yau; ta'porin tau iko'manpɨtʉ'pʉ, Aisi' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Seko' pokon nɨ nɨrɨ uko'mamʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ kasa, mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' eponin nan ipokon pe,\x - \xo 11:9 \xt Iseneses 35:27\x* 
\v 10 apʉne pʉra eke pata, tapon kenan, Papa nʉkoneka'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inamɨ'pʉ enupɨkɨrɨ tesi kon wenai. 
\p  
\v 11 Apurɨto' winɨ Epʉra'an, ipan pe kɨɨyi' pe kuru rɨ iyenasa' e'tane—mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Sera rɨ kanan e'tane umu'tan poken pʉra rɨ—to' rɨ umu'ta'pʉ, apʉne pʉra tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ Papa esi tukai' apurɨ iya wenai.  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ kasa si pʉse rɨ tikin nan nɨ ka'pon apai, iyeri'sa' pe rɨ te'sen apai rɨ, tu'ke rɨ ipayan ton e'seporo'pʉ mɨrɨ, itu'kanoro i'tu poken pʉra rɨ, sirikɨ amʉ' ka' awon kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wɨ'sɨ' parau e'pi pon kasa rɨ.\x - \xo 11:12 \xt Iseneses 15:5; 22:17; 32:12\x* 
\p  
\v 13 Tanporo pʉsamoro ka'pon amʉ' uko'mamʉ rɨ esi'pʉ apurɨto' winɨ tʉuma'ta kon a'tai rɨ. Usauro'nɨsa' ipɨ' rʉ'pʉ eporo'pʉ to' uya pen nɨ; to' uya rɨken ene'pʉ ɨnnonsi'kɨ mɨrɨpan ereutanʉkʉ'pʉ to' uya. To' uya ekama'pʉ serɨ non esi tʉpata kon pe pʉra tukai'.\x - \xo 11:13 \xt Iseneses 23:4; 1 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 29:15; Eren 39:12\x* 
\v 14 Ka'pon amʉ' mɨrɨ tawon nan esi tʉpata kon kuru enupɨkɨrɨ te'san pe.  
\v 15 Tʉnnɨmɨnʉ kon tʉpata kon pɨ' to' usenuminka yau, to' rɨ enna'po'pʉ nesii'no.  
\v 16 E'tane ru'ku, wakʉ kuru pata, Epʉn pon enupɨkɨrɨ to' esi. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Papa ɨpiyɨtʉ pen nɨ, to' e'to' itese' pɨ' ta a'tai tʉpɨ', apʉne pʉra to' pata konekasa' tʉuya pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 17 Apurɨto' winɨ Epʉra'an, Papa uya ti'tupɨtʉ a'tai, uya Aisi' tʉrʉ'pʉ tʉuse'mato' ike pe. Kʉrɨ rɨ si usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ eponin nʉ'pʉ esi'pʉ tikin nan nɨken tʉmu ke use'man pɨ',\x - \xo 11:17 \xt Iseneses 22:1-14\x* 
\v 18 Papa uya rɨ, “Aisi' winɨ usauro'nɨsa' kon ipɨ' apayan ton uyepʉ mɨrɨ,”\f + \fr 11:18 \ft Iseneses 21:12\f* tasa' e'tane.  
\v 19 Epʉra'an uya i'tu Papa uya rɨ Aisi' i'mʉ'sa'ka ima'tato' apai tukai', Papa uya rɨ si Aisi' i'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ iyerikʉ'pʉ apai kasa rɨ si. 
\p  
\v 20 Apurɨto' winɨ Aisi' uya Seko' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ I'sa pʉrema'pʉ mɨrɨ enta' to' uko'manto' pɨ'.\x - \xo 11:20 \xt Iseneses 27:27-29, 39-40\x* 
\p  
\v 21 Apurɨto' winɨ Seko' uya terikʉ a'tai Isose' munkɨ amʉ' pʉrema'pʉ to' kaisa rɨ, mɨrɨpan e'tʉnkasa' tʉteke'semu putu pona uya Papa apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 11:21 \xt Iseneses 47:31 (LXX); 48:1-20\x* 
\p  
\v 22 Apurɨto' winɨ Isose', a'ko pe tʉweyu esi pɨ', isaurokʉ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' utɨto' pɨ' Isi' apai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉyɨ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ ato' pe to' uya ta'kɨrɨ'nokon to' auro'ka'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 11:22 \xt Iseneses 50:24-25; E'sotas 13:19\x* 
\p  
\v 23 Apurɨto' winɨ Mosi' sanon uya onamʉ'pʉ osorʉwau kapʉi iyentu'pʉ awonsi'kɨ, apʉne pʉra wakʉ pe rʉ'kwɨ iyesi ene'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan kon esi'pʉ kin maimu pɨ' to' enari'nʉmʉ pʉra rɨ.\x - \xo 11:23 \xt E'sotas 2:2; 1:22\x* 
\p  
\v 24 Apurɨto' winɨ Mosi' esi'pʉ, tʉusemo'kasa' a'tai, Peero ensi mʉre ta i'se pʉra tʉpɨ'.\x - \xo 11:24 \xt E'sotas 2:10-12\x* 
\v 25 Papa munkɨ amʉ' pokon pe tʉkota'mato' pe iye'kuu'pʉ, makoi eseru yau pori' pe tʉuko'mamʉ namai' aka'ne' pe rɨ.  
\v 26 Kʉrai pɨkɨrɨ sapeman nɨto' esi epe'kena' pe Isi' pon mamin entai tukai' i'tu tʉuya ke, apʉne pʉra tepe'pʉ ɨnepopai tesi pɨ'.  
\v 27 Apurɨto' winɨ Isi' nɨmɨ'pʉ iya, kin sakorooi pɨ' te'namai' pʉra; sa'man annau rɨ apʉne pʉra tʉusensen pen ensa' tʉuya pɨ'.  
\v 28 Apurɨto' winɨ To' Epoi Itɨto' pɨ' enta'nan nɨto' tɨpiyarʉka'pʉ iya. Mɨrɨ a'tai, mʉn pai'pai'mato' pe mʉra'ta wakapuri pona to' uya ikuu'pʉ iya, wapiya iyentusa' ma'tanʉ'nin uya wapiya iyentusa' Esuwerʉ amʉ' mʉre ma'tanʉkʉ namai'.\x - \xo 11:28 \xt E'sotas 12:21-30\x*\fig Mʉn pai'pai'mato' pe mʉra'ta wakapuri pona to' uya ikuu'pʉ iya.|src="CN02096B.tif" size="col" loc="HEB 11:28" copy="David C. Cook" ref="11:28" \fig* 
\p  
\v 29 Apurɨto' winɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' uya Isuweyu Parau nɨ'kwɨrɨ'nʉkʉ'pʉ a'mun non poro utɨn kasa rɨ; mɨrɨ kupʉ i'se Isi' pon kon e'tane, to' aputa'pʉ.\x - \xo 11:29 \xt E'sotas 14:21-31\x* 
\p  
\v 30 Apurɨto' winɨ Iseri'ko wekupiri uta'mo'ka'pʉ, 7 kaisa rɨ wʉi iwoi Esuwerʉ amʉ' utɨpɨtʉ'pʉ e'sorʉ'mai'ma tʉpo.\x - \xo 11:30 \xt Isa'suwa 6:12-21\x*\fig Iseri'ko wekupiri uta'mo'ka'pʉ, 7 kaisa rɨ wʉi iwoi Esuwerʉ amʉ' utɨpɨtʉ'pʉ e'sorʉ'mai'ma tʉpo.|src="CN02100B.tif" size="col" loc="HEB 11:30" copy="David C. Cook" ref="11:30" \fig* 
\p  
\v 31 Apurɨto' winɨ Reyapu, pʉrata pɨkɨrɨ tekumasen, wɨnɨ pʉra iyesi'pʉ, main awɨron kon pen pokon pe, apʉne pʉra, ama'ai non ense itɨsa' kon ereutanʉ'sa' iya pɨ'.\x - \xo 11:31 \xt Isa'suwa 2:1-21; 6:22-25\x* 
\p  
\v 32 Ɨ'rɨ ta uya mɨrɨ enta'? Uweyu pʉra man, Kitiyan pɨ', Para' pɨ', Sansʉn pɨ', Ise'ta pɨ', Tepi' pɨ', Sanwerʉ pɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'kena' amʉ' pɨ' usaurokʉ weyu,\x - \xo 11:32 \xt Eseru Aimenkanin Nan 6:11—8:32; 4:6—5:31; 13:2—16:31; 11:1—12:7; 1 Sanwerʉ 16:1—1 Kin Amʉ' 2:11; 1 Sanwerʉ 1:1—25:1\x* 
\v 33 apurɨto' winɨ esa' wannɨ pe te'sen pata ton mo'kapɨ'nin nʉ'san, ɨsi'kaisa rɨ ekamʉra te'san tʉrawasomapɨ'nin nʉ'san, usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' epopɨ'nin nʉ'san; rayan amʉ' mʉta a'kopɨ'nin nʉ'san,\x - \xo 11:33 \xt Taniyerʉ 6:1-27\x* 
\v 34 apo' i'nɨ'panʉ'pɨ'nin nʉ'san, supara yɨ apai iyainʉnsa' kon; ɨ'sɨ'mʉra to' e'to' enapɨ'sa' rʉ'san meruntɨ pe; pana' pe to' enapɨtʉ'pʉ to' usewa'noma a'tai, mɨrɨpan kon enapɨtʉ'pʉ ɨnnon kon soisaai amʉ' entai kuru.\x - \xo 11:34 \xt Taniyerʉ 3:1-30\x* 
\v 35 Uri'sami'si amʉ' uya iyeri'sa' kon tʉtonpa kon e'mʉ'sa'kasa' epopɨtʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 11:35 \xt 1 Kin Amʉ' 17:17-24; 2 Kin Amʉ' 4:25-37\x* Tʉron kon kota'ma'pʉ ipan pe tʉnonka kon i'se pʉra to' esi pɨ', wakʉ te'mʉ'sa'kato' kon epoto' pe tʉuya'nokon te'san terikʉ kon tʉpo.  
\v 36 Tʉron kon uya tʉpatakapɨtʉ kon moronka'pʉ tari'po'pɨtʉ kon, tʉron kon auronpɨtʉ'pʉ pariki'si ta' to' tʉpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 11:36 \xt 1 Kin Amʉ' 22:26-27; 2 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 18:25-26; Iseremaya 20:2; 37:15; 38:6\x* 
\v 37 To' wɨnɨ'pʉ tɨ' ke; to' sara'mo'pʉ saka ke a'sa'mʉyai; supara ke to' wɨnɨ'pʉ. To' upinimʉ'pʉ karimeru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kapirita pi'pɨ ipon pe, entu'ma', ikota'masa' pe e'ne' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri pe rɨ iku'sa' pe—\x - \xo 11:37 \xt 2 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 24:21\x*\fig Esuwerʉ amʉ' uya Isuweyu Parau nɨ'kwɨrɨ'nʉkʉ'pʉ a'mun non poro utɨn kasa rɨ.|src="CN02098B.tif" size="span" loc="HEB 11:29" copy="David C. Cook" ref="11:29" \fig* 
\v 38 non esi'pʉ wakʉ pe pʉra rɨ to' pona. To' usarɨ'pʉ te'ma ke pʉra rɨ rɨmono'ta awɨrɨ, wʉ' poro'ne rɨ, tɨ' euta nau'ne rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non euta nau'ne rɨ. 
\p  
\v 39 Tanporo pʉsamoro apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya apurɨto' pɨkɨrɨ, e'tane ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ipɨ' usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ eporo'pʉ pen nɨ.  
\v 40 Papa uya mɨrɨ entaino kuru wakʉ konekasa' uiwano' kon pe, urɨ'nokon pokon pe rɨken to' ekonekasa' e'to' pe wakʉ pe. 
\c 12  
\s1 Papa Uya Tʉmunkɨ Amʉ' Koneka Main Awɨron Kon Pe 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe si iyesi pɨ', tu'ke kuru rɨ kamoro iye'kupʉ tʉnene'pʉ kon ekamanin nan esi pɨ' uwoi'nokon, eno'mapai'nokon tanporon nɨ uko'manʉkʉ kon pɨ' na'ne' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi upɨ'nokon ita'sisa' na'ne' sa'man pe rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eka'tun nɨpai'nokon ikupʉ uya kuru tai'ma eka'tun nɨto' iyawɨrɨ pe iye'ma'kʉmasa' na'ne' awɨrɨ.  
\v 2 Sises pɨ' uyenu kon tʉtʉse e'nɨpai'nokon, apurɨto' piya'tɨnin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe ikonekanin nʉ'pʉ, pori' pe te'to' esi pɨ' tʉrau kurusu' moronkanin nʉ'pʉ, ɨpiyɨ'nɨto' tʉnamai' pʉra rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ si Papa apon enwo'netʉ winɨ iyereuta'pʉ.  
\v 3 Serɨ moronka'pʉ iya pɨ' tewa'noma tane tʉmakooikena' nan ka'pon amʉ' uya pɨ' ɨsenuminkatɨ', ɨuseta'ka kon namai' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨyewan kon mo'ka auya'nokon namai'. 
\p  
\v 4 Makoi ya' ɨusewa'noma kon e'suranma yau, ɨmʉnʉ kon enno'ka'sa' auya'nokon pʉra man.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ main, “Umunkɨ amʉ',” tawon pu'tɨka'nʉ'sa' auya'nokon ɨpori'mapɨ'nin kon pe te'sen: 
\q1 “Mooi, usennakan pe Itepuru uya main awɨron pe ɨkonekato' kʉ'kupʉi, 
\q2 ɨyewan kʉ'mo'kai ɨyeseremekʉ iya a'tai, 
\q1  
\v 6 apʉne pʉra Itepuru kʉrɨ rɨ tʉni'nʉnkanʉ ton konekanin main awɨron kon pe, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon tʉmu pe tʉnanʉmʉnʉ ton kota'ma iya,”\x - \xo 12:6 \xt Isopu 5:17\x*\f + \fr 12:6 \ft Ipu'ketʉ 3:11-12 (LXX)\f* 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 7 Sa'man imoronkatɨ' main awɨron kon pe ɨkoneka kon pe; Papa uya enpoika tʉmunkɨ pe ɨwe'to' kon pe. Ɨnʉ' moro mʉre esi'pʉ ikʉipʉnʉ nʉkonekanʉ pen main awɨrɨ iye'to' pe?  
\v 8 Main awɨron pe tʉkonekasan pe pʉra ɨwesi kon yau (tʉron kon koneka koro'tau main awɨron pe), pʉrau pe rɨ nin ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ, i'nairon kon imunkɨ pe ɨwesi kon pen nɨ.  
\v 9 Tʉkʉipʉnʉ kenan kon urɨ'nokon main awɨron pe ukonekanin kon, mɨrɨ pɨ' nin si to' namanin nan urɨ'nokon. Mɨrɨ entai nin si, Epʉn pon Kʉipʉnʉ wannɨ ena' e'tʉn nɨto' pe iyesi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uko'man nɨto' pe!  
\v 10 Ukʉipʉnʉ kon uya main awɨron kon pe ukoneka kon aka'nero' pe rɨ, wakʉ pe tʉpona'nokon te'sen awɨrɨ; e'tane Papa uya main awɨron pe ukoneka kon wakʉ pe uku'nin kon pe, wakʉ pe iye'to' yau ipokon pe e'nɨto' pe.  
\v 11 Main awɨron pe e'nɨto' pe konekan a'tai wakʉ pe pona wannɨ iyesi pen nɨ, e'tane e'ne' pe rɨ. E'tane rɨ emennʉ'pʉ ipokena' awɨrɨ te'sen pe e'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' akʉ'pɨ'nʉkʉ iya kamoro iwinɨ isenupasa' kon iwano' pe. 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', kʉkʉkʉ pe te'sen ɨyemekon kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨ'sɨ'mʉn ɨyese'mu kon imeruntɨtanʉ'tɨ'.\x - \xo 12:12 \xt Aisaya 35:3\x* 
\v 13 “Ɨsi'kaisa rɨ a'ta kon e'ma ikonekatɨ',”\f + \fr 12:13 \ft Ipu'ketʉ 4:26 (LXX)\f* ise'mesa' pe te'sen utakonomapɨtʉ namai', e'tane isepi'tɨto' pe. 
\s1 Panaman Papa Nurunpanin Pe E'nɨ Namai' 
\p  
\v 14 Tʉusi'tui' ɨko'mantɨ' tʉusewankamai' pʉra tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' pokon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe te'san pe; wakʉ pe te'san pe pʉra esii'ma, ɨnʉ' yan uya Itepuru ene pʉra iyesi.  
\v 15 Tense e'tɨ' ɨnʉ' uya rɨ wakʉ nonkasa' Papa uya pʉremekʉ namai', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'ne' mi' rɨ kʉsa'tanin ekamʉn ku'ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tu'kan kon ma'tanʉ'ton pe.\x - \xo 12:15 \xt Isu'taronomi 29:18 (LXX)\x* 
\v 16 Entɨ' ɨnʉ' rɨ esi namai' tekumasen pe, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Papa i'tunin pe pʉra I'sa kasa, tikin ite'kwa rɨ tenta'nato' epe' pe irui pe tesi neporonʉ kuru kʉrʉpo'pomanin kasa.\x - \xo 12:16 \xt Iseneses 25:29-34\x* 
\v 17 Mɨrɨ pata'pʉ pe, mi'tuyatʉi'ne' kasa, serɨ si tʉpʉremato' eporo i'se iyesi a'tai, inurunpa'pʉ si. Inkuu'pʉ rʉ'pʉ enna'po poken pʉra iyesi'pʉ, tʉukaranse tʉpʉremato' warinpa tane iya rɨ.\f + \fr 12:17 \fq tʉneporonʉ warinpa tane iya rɨ; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tʉpʉremato' eporo i'se iye'tane.\f*\x - \xo 12:17 \xt Iseneses 27:30-40\x* 
\p  
\v 18 Wʉ' piya' ɨuye'sa' kon pen ta'pɨ'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' nʉpo'tɨnʉ; ewarupɨ ya', ipan ewarupɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pana'pan a'setun;  
\v 19 tʉronpi' uturunto' ya', mɨrɨ pe pʉra main usetato' ya', etanin nan e'to' miyarɨ ɨnetapai pʉra ya',\x - \xo 12:19 \xt E'sotas 19:16-22; 20:18-21; Isu'taronomi 4:11-12; 5:22-27\x* 
\v 20 apʉne pʉra tapiyo'masa' kon ipɨ' moronka tʉuya'nokon poken pʉra iyesi pɨ': “O' uya rɨ wʉ' a'pɨ'sa' pe iyesi yau, tɨ' ke iwɨto' pe iyesi,”\f + \fr 12:20 \ft E'sotas 19:12-13\f* tawon.  
\v 21 Nari'pa' rɨ iyesi'pʉ, Mosi' uya, “Etʉipɨtʉ utɨtɨtɨma pɨ' man,”\f + \fr 12:21 \ft Isu'taronomi 9:19\f* ta'pʉ mɨrɨ pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 22 E'tane Sayan Wʉpʉ pona ɨuye'sa' kon, Epʉn pe te'sen Surusiran pona, nurɨnan Papa pata'se' eke kuru ya'. Tu'kan kon, tu'kan kon inserʉ amʉ' pori' pe iyamʉrasa' kon piya' ɨuye'sa' kon,  
\v 23 iyɨmʉrewato' ton imunkɨ amʉ' so'sii ta', itese' iye'menukapɨ'sa' kon Epʉn po. Papa piya' ɨuye'sa' kon, tanporon kon eseru aimenkanin piya', ipokena' kon nʉ'san a'kwarʉ'pʉ ton ekonekasa' wakʉ pe piya',  
\v 24 Sises emenna' ekonekan nɨto' tʉneporo'pʉ tʉnin piya', mʉn pai'pai'masa' wakʉ pe parɨ imaimu tʉusauro'sen Eperʉ mʉnʉ entai.\x - \xo 12:24 \xt Iseneses 4:10\x* 
\p  
\v 25 Entɨ' kʉrɨ tʉusauro'sen nurunpa auya'nokon namai'. To' ainʉmʉ poken pʉra iye'sa' yau, kʉrɨ non po tʉpanamanin kon tʉnurunpai', mɨrɨ o'koi' pe' e'nɨ'nokon upanamanin kon Epʉn poi piyapai era'tɨn nɨsa'nokon yau?\x - \xo 12:25 \xt E'sotas 20:22\x* 
\v 26 Mɨrɨ a'tai, imaimu uya non i'ki'ma'pʉ, e'tane si serɨ pe isauro'sa' ikupʉ tʉuya pɨ', “Serɨ rɨken pe non nɨken i'ki'ma uya pen, e'tane ka' rɨ nɨrɨ,”\f + \fr 12:26 \ft Akiyai 2:6 (LXX)\f* tasa' iya.  
\v 27 Main ton, “Serɨ rɨken pe,” nɨkayai'ne' uya ekama tʉusi'ki'masen pe te'sen ama—ika'sa' ton pe te'sen—tʉusi'ki'masen ton pen nin si e'to' pe moro. 
\p  
\v 28 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', tesa' ke e'nɨto' yau tʉusi'ki'masen pen eporo pɨ', tenki tapai'nokon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa apurɨpɨ'pai'nokon ipori'manin pe inama mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe i'tuto' winɨ,  
\v 29 apʉne pʉra, “Papa, itese' pɨ' e'nɨto' esi ma'tanʉ'nin apo' pe rɨ,”\f + \fr 12:29 \ft Isu'taronomi 4:24\f* tasa' iya. 
\c 13  
\s1 Iu'matʉ Pe Panaman Nɨto' 
\p  
\v 1 Tʉusi'nʉnkai' e'tɨ' ɨsitonpa pe.  
\v 2 Kɨpu'tɨka'tʉu ka'kʉran amʉ' ereutanʉ'to' pɨ', mɨrɨ ku'nin nan tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' uya inserʉ amʉ' ereutanʉkʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ i'tui'ma pʉra.\x - \xo 13:2 \xt Iseneses 18:1-8; 19:1-3\x* 
\v 3 Pariki'si ta' a'sisa' kon tʉku'se ɨyenu kon yau, to' pokon pe rɨ a'sisa' pe ɨwesi kon pe te'ku'se, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro ɨsɨ pe tʉkota'masan, ɨmɨrɨ'nokon nɨ ekota'ma pe. 
\p  
\v 4 Tanporon kon emari'man nɨto' namai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyemari'masa' kon nesii tʉmaimu rʉ'pʉ kon awɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra temari'masa' e'tane iyekumasa' rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo tekumasan eseru aimenkato' oton Papa uya pɨ'.  
\v 5 Pʉrata wenai tʉuta'kwarʉkai' pʉra ɨko'mantɨ', ɨyenau'nokon na'ne' pɨ' rɨ tepori'mai' e'tɨ', apʉne pʉra Papa uya, 
\q1 “Ɨnɨmɨ uya pʉra kuru iyesi; 
\q2 ɨnonka uya pʉra kuru iyesi,”\f + \fr 13:5 \ft Isu'taronomi 31:6, 8\f* 
\m tasa'.\x - \xo 13:5 \xt Isa'suwa 1:5\x* 
\v 6 Uyenu kon yau si esii'ma ta serɨ, 
\q1 “Itepuru esi upika'tɨnin pe; enari'nʉmʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi. 
\q2 Ɨ'rɨ pe ken ka'pon uya ukupʉ?”\f + \fr 13:6 \ft Eren 118:6-7 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta'nokon. 
\p  
\v 7 Ɨyepuru kon amʉ' iku'tɨ' ɨyenu kon yau, Papa Maimu ekamanin nʉ'san ɨpɨ'nokon. To' uko'mamʉ'pʉ otori'pɨ pɨ' ɨsenuminkatɨ', to' uya apurɨto' ipatakapɨ'tɨ'.  
\v 8 Sises Kʉrai kʉrɨ rɨ, kʉrɨ rɨ rɨ ko'mamiyau iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inkero' rɨ. 
\p  
\v 9 Ti'tui' pʉra rɨ ti'tupɨ'sen pen nɨ enupan nɨto' ayano'matɨ'nin. Wakʉ pe rɨ iyesi uyewan kon umeruntɨtato' pe wakʉ nonkasa' ke, kiyari rɨ pɨ' teseru ke e'nɨto' winɨ pen, ipɨ' tenta'nasan pika'tɨnin pen nɨ.  
\v 10 Moro use'man nɨto' apon esi ipoi kamoro ta'porin tau te'tʉrawasomasan enta'nato' itau pen nɨ. 
\p  
\v 11 Use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya o' mʉnʉ rʉ'pʉ arɨ Ipan Wakʉ Kuru Pata ya' makoi ku'sa' epe'pʉ pe tʉtʉsen, e'tane nin ipun nʉ'pʉ po'tɨ ɨnnɨ rɨ pʉroroi apai.\x - \xo 13:11 \xt Ripaiti'kas 16:27\x* 
\v 12 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, Sises ekota'ma'pʉ e'ne' pe eke kuru pata mʉra'taai pʉroroi entau, wakʉ pe tʉmunkɨ amʉ' ekonekato' pe tʉmʉnʉ winɨ.  
\v 13 Utɨnpai'nokon ipiya' ɨnnɨ pata apai, ipiyɨ'nʉ'nin pe te'sen moronkai'.  
\v 14 Apʉne pʉra serɨ yau inke tʉuko'mansen eke upata kon pʉra iyesi, e'tane tʉuye'ton eke pata enupɨkɨrɨ e'nɨ'nokon serɨ. 
\p  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Sises poro miyarɨ rɨ Papa ena' use'man pe apurɨpɨ'pai'nokon—mʉta tʉrawasooi winɨ itese' pɨ' tʉsauro'sen.  
\v 16 Wakʉ ku'to' auya'nokon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨtonpa kon pokon pe te'repai' ɨwe'to' kon kʉ'pu'tɨka'nʉ'tʉu, serɨ warai use'man nɨto' esi Papa pori'manin pe.  
\v 17 Ɨyepuru kon amʉ' maimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ', to' pana'pano o'no te'tʉse e'tɨ'. Apa'sima kon pɨ' to' esi, tʉusekama ton kon pe Papa pana ya'. To' maimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ' to' tʉrawasooi e'to' pe pori' pe e'nɨto' pe, e'tape'ne' pe pʉra, mɨrɨ uya ɨpika'tɨ kon pʉra iyesi. 
\p  
\v 18 Ina pona ɨpʉrematɨ'. Ina uya i'tu ina ewan esi wakʉ pe, ekamʉn ku'sa' ina uya pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon yau rɨ wakʉ pe tʉnamasan pe ɨko'manpaino kon pe.  
\v 19 Ɨyekama'po uya 'nokon kuru ɨwɨpʉrema kon pa, ɨpiya'nokon enna'poto' pe inke pʉra. 
\p  
\v 20 Tɨwɨ Papa tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' esa', siyaro' pe ekonekan nɨto' mʉnʉ poro iyeri'sa' uyepuru kon Sises i'mʉ'sa'kanin nʉ'pʉ, kʉrɨ rɨ eke kuru karimeru amʉ' Pa'simanin,  
\v 21 ɨrepai'nokon tanporon wakʉ ton ke i'se iye'to' kupʉ kon pa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨwɨ uyau'nokon nʉtʉrawasomai tʉpori'manin pe te'sen, Sises Kʉrai poro, itiwano' pe eke pe iku'to' nesii, inke rɨ, inke rɨ. Amen. 
\p  
\v 22 Utonpa ton, ipan pe ɨyekama'po uya 'nokon apanamato' kon uya eta kon pa, apʉne pʉra to'ken nʉ'kwɨ rɨ kareta menukasa' uya ɨyena'nokon. 
\p  
\v 23 I'tu auya'nokon i'se e'ai' utonpa ton Temu'ti si nonkasa' man. Serɨ pe iwa iye'sa' yau, iya'kɨrɨ utɨ mɨrɨ ɨyense'nokon. 
\p  
\v 24 Miyarɨ ka'tɨ' ɨyepuru kon amʉ' pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo Papa munkɨ amʉ' pɨ'. Kamoro I'tari winon kon miyarɨ nɨkayan ɨpɨ'nokon. 
\p  
\v 25 Wakʉ nonkasa' nesii ɨpiyau'nokon.